        "client_msg_id": "76A5ABB8-7F14-45B7-852E-1B9155A7D465",
        "type": "message",
        "text": "This is dumb, extortionist, and also completely expected. What frustrates me most is that the only function of publishers, really, is to curate playlists of academic papers into a single place. Literally every other function they serve can be replaced for free using existing open access or open source tools. And curation is possible too if a person or group is motivated and has the social capital. But this likely won’t change without government intervention (publish with a Dutch citizen\/academic and I believe the fees are waived), or with ECRs bucking the trend by publishing in free open access journals or self-publishing.",
