        "client_msg_id": "ED638168-E673-4727-B05D-09FF61B8598C",
        "type": "message",
        "text": "People on Twitter are suggesting that right now in response to this.\n\nThere’s also <https:\/\/twitter.com\/450movement?s=21|https:\/\/twitter.com\/450movement?s=21> which is about getting publishers to pay researchers for reviewing (they have contracts drafted up you can use), or <https:\/\/twitter.com\/redteammarket?s=21|https:\/\/twitter.com\/redteammarket?s=21> where you can hire (you set the amount with them, so it could be free) a team of experts to be critics of your work (including things like code review which never happens in traditional peer-review). Just as examples of how people are fed up with current science publishing models.\n\nPreprints exist so it’s not like you need to wait to publish your work anyways. And if you want your preprint peer-reviewed you could just ask someone in your field yourself (maybe offer to review one of their preprints in return; or pay them). Then append the review to your preprint; or have them do the peer-review in a GitHub issues post. So many options out there that don’t require choosing to be exploited and wasting taxpayer money.",
